---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Daniel Tse and the editorial direction behind danieltse.org.">
  <section class="page-lead">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Hands-on engineering leadership, documented from the implementation layer.</h1>
    <p class="page-lead-summary">
      I care about the seam between architecture intent and production reality: AI systems that
      behave under pressure, backend services that stay understandable, and cloud platforms that
      reduce operational drag instead of multiplying it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="copy-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>What this site is for</h2>
      <p>
        This is the canonical home for my writing and the narrative layer around the projects that
        back it up. Long-form essays live here first. Project pages exist for shipped work with a
        real point of view, evidence, and a maintenance story.
      </p>
      <p>
        The editorial line is deliberate: practical systems thinking, implementation detail,
        project tradeoffs, and engineering judgment rather than generic trend commentary.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>What I write about</h2>
      <p>
        Expect essays on local LLMs, integration protocols, JVM and Kotlin backend work, cloud
        infrastructure, delivery pipelines, and the kind of operational details that decide whether
        an architecture is elegant only on slides or robust in production.
      </p>
      <p>
        Notes stay shorter and more tactical. Essays expand the reasoning. Project pages show the
        shipped systems, benchmarks, and tooling choices that give the writing teeth.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
